@startuml seq-revert
title Revert v1.2.0 - rotation + TTL backup + partial-failure rollback (Plane B / fromDbSeed=true)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Source app\n(db-seed loader)" as App
participant "propagateClientToApis\n(http/init)" as Propagate
database "Redis (source)" as RedisSrc
collections "Target A\n/api/internal/hmac" as TargetA
collections "Target B\n/api/internal/hmac" as TargetB
participant "handleInternalManagementRequest" as Handler
database "Redis (target A)" as RedisA
database "Redis (target B)" as RedisB

== Step 1: rotation with fromDbSeed=true ==
App -> Propagate : propagateClientToApis({\n  operation: "update",\n  clientId: "bizClient",\n  secret: "NEW",\n  fromDbSeed: true,\n  targets: [A, B]\n})

note over Propagate
  Local side-effect on the source store:
  clients.setSecret(..., { fromDbSeed: true })
  writes a TTL backup of the previous
  secretHash in:
   <namespace>:credentials-backup:bizClient
  EX dbSeedBackupTtlSeconds (default 600)
end note
Propagate -> RedisSrc : SET credentials-backup:bizClient = OLD_HASH EX 600

== Step 2: wire to each target ==
Propagate -> TargetA : PUT /api/internal/hmac\nBody: { clientId, secretHash: NEW_HASH, allowedIps, fromDbSeed: true }
TargetA -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest
Handler -> RedisA : HGET clients[bizClient]\nreturns { secretHash: OLD_HASH, fromDbSeed: ... }
note right of Handler
  fromDbSeed === true AND
  existing AND
  existing.secretHash !== NEW_HASH
  -> write backup BEFORE the HSET
end note
Handler -> RedisA : SET credentials-backup:bizClient = OLD_HASH EX 600
Handler -> RedisA : HSET clients[bizClient] = { secretHash: NEW_HASH, fromDbSeed: true, ... }
Handler --> Propagate : 201 { operation: "update", accepted: true }

Propagate -> TargetB : PUT /api/internal/hmac\nBody: { clientId, secretHash: NEW_HASH, allowedIps, fromDbSeed: true }
TargetB --> Propagate : 0 / 4xx / 5xx (refused for any reason)

== Step 3: source classifies and decides ==
Propagate -> App : results=[{target:A, accepted:true}, {target:B, accepted:false}]
note over App
  Mixed result on a fromDbSeed plan:
  - acceptedTargets = [A]
  - refusedTargets  = [B]
  Trigger rollback.
end note

== Step 4: REVERT on accepted targets (Scenario 1) ==
App -> Propagate : propagateClientToApis({\n  operation: "revert",\n  clientId: "bizClient",\n  targets: [A]\n})
Propagate -> TargetA : PATCH /api/internal/hmac\nBody: { clientId } (no secret, no allowedIps)
TargetA -> Handler : handleInternalManagementRequest (PATCH)
Handler -> RedisA : GET credentials-backup:bizClient -> OLD_HASH
Handler -> RedisA : HSET clients[bizClient] = { secretHash: OLD_HASH, ... }\nDEL credentials-backup:bizClient
Handler --> Propagate : 201 { operation: "revert", reverted: true }

== Step 5: REVERT locally on source ==
App -> RedisSrc : clients.revert("bizClient")\n(equivalent local rollback)
RedisSrc -> RedisSrc : restore OLD_HASH, DEL local backup
note right of App
  Convergence:
  - source: OLD_HASH
  - target A: OLD_HASH (was bumped, then reverted)
  - target B: OLD_HASH (was never bumped)
  Federation back in sync. Next sync tick
  will retry with a fresh secret.
end note

== Safety fallback ==
note over RedisSrc, RedisB
  If the source crashes between step 2 and step 4,
  the credentials-backup TTL expires on its own
  on every target that still holds one. The lib
  then refuses to revert (reverted: false, no-op)
  and the federation lives with the new hash
  until the next sync tick decides otherwise.
end note

@enduml
